  "time_ut": 1662021249,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0da9\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dbb\u0dca \u0dc3\u0d82\u0da0\u0dd2\u0dad \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0d9a\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf \u0daf\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca \u0db1\u0ddc\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0db8\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dbd\u0dca \u0db8\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9\u0dbd\u0dba \u0d9a\u0dc5\u0dda \u0db6\u0dbb\u0db4\u0dad\u0dc5 \u0dc0\u0dbb\u0daf\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The monetary board made a serious mistake by not notifying the dollar reserves in advance",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "When the country's dollar reserve had fallen to twenty million US dollars, the Monetary Board of the Central Bank of Sri Lanka committed a serious and unforgivable mistake by not informing the House in advance, said Mr. Lakshman Kiriella, the main organizer of the opposition, in Parliament today (1).",
        "The chief organizer of the opposition said that when the Governor of the Central Bank of Sri Lanka, Dr. Nandalal Weerasinghe, came to the Parliament yesterday to deliver a speech, he questioned why the country's dollar reserve had fallen to twenty million US dollars and why he did not inform the Parliament about the situation and he got angry at his question.",
        "He said this during the second reading debate on the Budget Appropriation Bill.",
        "The central bank had a duty to inform the parliament about the country's dollar situation, but the central bank did not fulfill that duty. It is a very dangerous situation when the country handed over with 7800 million dollars is reduced to 20 million dollars. But the central bank did not give any notification to the parliament.",
        "Honorable Deputy Speaker, yesterday the Governor of the Central Bank came to Parliament to deliver a speech. He said that when he took office, the central bank had only 20 million dollars. 20 million is the cost of one day in our country. I asked him if he informed the parliament about this situation? Because the money power belongs to the Parliament. When we handed over the country, we handed over 7800 million dollars. When this amount goes down to 20 million, it is a very dangerous situation. I asked the governor of the central bank about this. When he was asked this question, he got annoyed.",
        "Don't we have a right to know about this money? We have a right, that's why I asked. The members of the ruling party thought that I was raising a political issue. The Governor did not give a proper answer.",
        "In fact, the president or the prime minister of the previous government did not say that the country was bankrupt. The central bank did not say either. It was only after Ranil Wickremesinghe became the prime minister that they said on TV that the country was bankrupt. That's when we also came to know that the central bank has worked without responsibility.",
        "Even during the war, about 500 to 600 million dollars came from foreign workers a year. Today, it is down to 1.5. The government is talking about investments, but they don't bring in the money of our foreign workers. Why is that? I am not sure. I am asking the government to make arrangements to bring this money, if we can do that, we can find our monthly expenses. But we have not been able to get even that money."
      ],
